                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/1246a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-01T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 1, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>826. At request of David MeKelvey White of Friends of Abraham Lincoln Brigade,
                    please report circumstances of and basic reason for reported action of French
                    authorities in refusing admission to group of wounded Americans from Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
